balanceOf(address,uint256).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOf}. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

params.fid_: target fid to trace path to from root

params.whoabout_: you care about them dont you

params.signals: array of signaling values constructed starting with membrane, inflation, and [redistributive preferences for sub-entities]

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.

getFidPath(uint256).notice: retrieves token path id array from root to target id

isMember(address,uint256).notice: checks if provided address who is member in where id

sendSignal(uint256,uint256[]).notice: processes and stores user signalin case threashold is reached, the change is applied.formatted as follows: membrane, inflation, [recognition]

totalSupplyOf(uint256).notice: stores the total supply of each id | id -> supply
